reviews.name: Jeanette R.
reviews.review:
We tried this place when we found out that our hotel was charging $75.00 a day!!  we were able to park our car for a total of 3 days and it was less then 1 day at the hotel.
We will definitely use ParkMe again!!

reviews.name: Jonathan D.
reviews.review: Wanted less expensive option for morning meeting at S.F.Public. It's about 8 blocks from the library-- I don't mind walking through the Tenderloin. Did see 2 cops running & 4 cop cars (wrong way through one-way traffic) take off in pursuit of a cell phone thief. Staff was polite and efficient. Cell phone check in with reservation was easy. They had my car at the front of the lot's 1st floor at the time I said I'd return. There's a little Burmese restaurant 2 blocks away on Eddy. Had nice hot bowl of catfish chowder before picking up the car.

reviews.name: Maya Y.
reviews.review: So glad we did this. Whenever we drive up to SF, we always end up wandering around and finding either sketchy or overpriced parking. This helped make pur day much less stressful and worrisome. The attendants were friendly and helpful, and happily took us up to the 2nd story when we wanted to drop off some stuff. Thank you!

reviews.name: Edward S.
reviews.review: Worked great. I'd suggest adding a map view when the list of search results comes up to make choosing a space a little easier. Will definitely use your service again.

reviews.name: Heather J.
reviews.review:
This was my first time using ParkMe, as I was driving up to San Francisco
for an all-day meeting and wanted to find reasonably-priced parking within
a couple blocks of the conference hotel. I didn't know reservations were a
new feature, but it was super helpful to be able to plan ahead and not
scramble for parking at 7:30AM. The website helped me find several garages
that were significantly better priced than the conference hotel. All I had
to do was show my reservation at the garage, and the attendants took care
of the rest.

reviews.name: Heather J.
reviews.review: I needed a parking spot for an all-day meeting at the Hilton Union Square, and I had no interest in paying $50+ to park in the hotel garage. Rock Star Parking was just a block or two away, easy to find, and the pre-booked price was great. The garage is in the Tenderloin, so the surroundings are a bit sketchy, but the attendants were professional and the garage felt totally secure. Would recommend.

reviews.name: Stephen P.
reviews.review: Great location if you are Looking for inexpensive parking near Market Street.

reviews.review: Great lot. Great price. Great location

reviews.name: C B.
reviews.review:
I would leave a negative review if I could. I stayed at the Parc 55 and had my car parked by valet. Upon returning my car, I had a ding in the passenger side door. I reported this immediately to an attendant. I later received a letter from Connecticut stating the ding was pre- existing (which is a highly incorrect statement). I asked for evidence to support this claim. The representative from Propark then emailed me a piece of paper from Propark with a car diagram on it with an X on the passenger side door. The representative stated this was the proof that the ding was pre- existing. Unbelievable! This was not a diagram filled out after a joint inspection by the attendant and myself in which I signed in agreement. This was offered after the fact. When I made the initial complaint at Parc 55, the supervisor took a report and did not even mention this "evidence". This evidence was created after the report was taken I am sure. Before I leave my car with any valet service, I walk around it in order to check the body. I take very good care of my car. Due to the valet service,
My family and I will never stay at this location again. Where is the honorable and just business practice? This whole experience was highly unsavory and dishonest.

reviews.name: Robert V.
reviews.review: We attempted to contact the parking personnel to arrange for monthly parking, using the number listed on the locator ad. All we received was a recording instructing us to "enter the extension that we want to leave a message for". How are we suppose to know the extension when none are listed?

reviews.name: Greg M.
reviews.review: We were catching a flight back to New Zealand at 9.45pm and needed somewhere to park our hire car. This garage which is well located, was easy to access and with valet parking it took a minute to drop off and two to three minutes for the car to be made available. Overall excellent experience.

reviews.name: Christoper L.
reviews.review: Sketchy neighborhood, empty lot on a weeknight, no listed prices and they wanted $40 for overnight parking. Avoid.

reviews.name: Yannick R.
reviews.review: Badest service I‘ve ever seen. Got our renting car, who was practically new. Let the car one night at the parking lot and there were scretchers on three rims!!! After a talk with the employee if they have an insurance or something, he got very unfriendly and talked about a lawyer…. 0 competence. Great start to our holidays….

reviews.name: Peggy S.
reviews.review: Parking was quick and easy; all I had to do was arrive, get out of my car, and hand it over to the valet. Leaving was just as quick and easy. The price was excellent for my Sunday sojourn to the Fairmont Hotel two blocks away (but, oh, those hills!). I would definitely use this service again.

reviews.name: Ramon H.
reviews.review: Great parking, great staff, no issues.

reviews.name: Barbara C.
reviews.review: This process -- of reserving and pre-paying for parking -- was so easy. It greatly increased my enjoyment of my trip to "The City," because I was not worried at all about finding a parking spot. The idea was good, and the implementation was great. Valet took care of everything on both arriving and leaving the lot. thank you!

reviews.name: Raymond H.
reviews.review: Whenever I visit San Francisco, I use this parking garage.  Mostly because of its location.  The garage is very clean and the security team is on duty paying close attention.  The early bird special fits my needs very well.

reviews.name: Sara R.
reviews.review: Myself and three others just left an event at the Masonic. The event staff inside the venue were fantastic, however the parking staff in the Masonic parking lot treated us terribly. Upon entry to our event (VIP dashboard confessional and third eye blind event) there was a sign posted saying event parking was $30.  We also received an email from live nation stating the parking was $30. When we paid we were charged $38. The parking attendant called the lot manager, who was EXTREMELY rude to us. He was rude, and talked down to us like a bully and said there was no sign because the event didn't start until 4, when in fact the VIP event started much earlier. He told us too bad, and that he's the manager and no one is going to give us our money back. We asked him if he put up the sign himself and he said no. He said "well did you take a picture of the sign? Do you have proof?" He was really mean to us, all over a measly $8. We are more upset over how degrading his speech was than the money itself. We are surely never parking in this parking garage again. He also refused to give our parking ticket back, and when we tried to leave he wouldn't let us out and made us back up and go around just to be rude. We felt like he basically told us to f-off. (Sorry about the language)

reviews.review:
In my opinion, the people in the garage are extremely nice!  Now there can be improvements but overall, its a good garage to park.  I just don't know why people don't like it.

Feedback:
1. Prices could be lowered
2. Could use a little training on new cars
3. Could try NOT to leave the windows open for flies and dust

reviews.name: Jennie P.
reviews.review: I went monthly at state garage in january 2015 up to May 3 2015. I had no problems all attendants were professionals treated me kindly and were highly informative of monthly rate  how to pay and what was expected. My number was 576 and I truly respect these men who job is customer service with positive attitude and kindness since all they do is park cars and retrieve autos to person daily. I had no problem  all workers from time of open to close were just remarkably respectful professionals with sense of humor. They have rules posted  as you enter the garage. I will always park my car at the state garage whenever I'm in the nob hill neighborhood.

reviews.name: Andrew G.
reviews.review: I asked the attendant the charge for parking overnight, to which he answered $30.00.  I told him I would need three days, so he told me it would be $90.00 (made sense).  When I came back the next day and told him I only needed two days, he quickly told me that two days was $45.00 per day (the same as three).  I asked him to show me where that was posted and he could not.  He became very upset and told me to be quiet and listen to him.  I told him that I thought he was very dishonest (and a few other things) and left.  I am currently disputing this with my credit card company.

reviews.name: L D.
reviews.review:
There was a misunderstanding about me taking my car vs. needing to grab something.  When the manager found out I was simply grabbing something, he lost it on me, started yelling, told me to get out, told me my month contract was cancelled (I was only three days in), and told me to leave.  He tried to reach into my car to grab the monthly parking permit from my rear window, which I obviously need to get a refund.

A few notes- The garage was very busy and I waited for 15 minutes while they attended to other customers and grabbed my car.  I understand they were really busy, so told them not to worry, that I would park my car on the street and then return later in the evening.  This didn't keep the manager from yelling at me.  He escalated the situation, told me my contract was "cancelled".

I returned to ask for a refund for the days I wont be using.  The manager claimed he can't process the refund, that it needs to come from the management office, and that I would only get 50% back.

reviews.review: The valet employees here will steal items out of your car.  Last night they stole my iPhone charge, change from my car, a cosmetics case, and my jacket. reviews.name: Roy D.
reviews.review: Was quoted $50 for parking for the day, $40 if I prepaid in cash which I did and when I returned I found out that the valet driver backed my car into a wall and caused considerable damage.  They refused to acknowledge that they caused the damage and said that it existed prior.

reviews.name: Judy F.
reviews.review: We had a terrible experience with this garage - we had a pre-paid, guaranteed reservation which they would not honor because they supposedly had to save the open spaces for a convention.  They claimed it was the (absent) owner's fault. Then in front of us they told another family that THEIR pre-paid reservation would also not be honored, but for $20 CASH they could have a spot. Sounded like a scam to us. Will not be back.

reviews.name: Walter G.
reviews.review:
Parked car at 9am on a Saturday for a $45.00 fee for 24 hours. I picked it up at 10:15 the next day.  The rates are posted, however, when you check your car in they do not review them with you. Very quick to tell you $45 for 24 hours. Rasheed and Kamel blame the price gouging on their computer and will tell you it comes out of their pay if they adjust it. Not their fault I suppose. Owners rules.
I parked my car there from 8:30am on Saturday to 10:00am on sunday (25 1/2 hours and it cost me $77.50.
LET THE BUYER BEWARE.  All legal I guess but if you can park somewhere else you will avoid the shifty PRICE GOUGING here.

reviews.review: Would give zero stars if I could. Tried parking here last night for a show at Regency Ballroom. I'm all smiles and laughing and in good spirit despite, say I am going to show will be back, no problem, etc. In the meantime he's asking me why I don't park in the street, says there's parking there, etc etc. I'm like, I'm in a rush already and feel safer leaving my car in garage. He takes my $20, continues blabbering, saying I could park in the street. I'm just laughing nicely still, again point out I'm in a rush would prefer to park and go. Ask about the hours posted. He's like, 11:45 is when YOU must be here, midnight is when I GO HOME. I'm just like okay, no problem, maybe should change the signs to reflect actual business hours, all very nicely. At that point he tells me to leave, to go park on the street. Rudely and curtly. I'm like, still super friendly, but I ask him, what? Are you serious? You don't want my money? You don't want my business? Really? He responds no, continues being a jerk, hands me my $20 back and watched as I had to back up down the long narrow entrance and leave. reviews.name: Marlene P.
reviews.review: I parked in this garage from 4:24 to 6:40 p.m. yesterday.  It features an automated parking system called Autopark and is under the auspices of Ace Parking of San Francisco.  I paid in case at the machine in the lobby of the building and was charged the exorbitant sum of $27.  That's bad enough.  I paid with two $20 bills.  After I'd inserted the first $20, the machine prompted me to insert more money.  After inserting the second $20, I was informed that the machine owed me $13.  It returned only $8.  While I was reacting to that, the robovoice inside the thieving device asked if I wanted a receipt.  Before I could press the button, the machine cut off access to it and returned to its resting state, leaving me without either the $5 it had stolen from me or the receipt.  I want my $5 back and I should like to know that someone is investigating this machine to determine what is wrong with its settings.  It may well be doing this to a large number of people every day, exacting its own robo-tolls.  I know it's only $5, but I am not willing to let this go and will press Ace Parking to correct this situation.
